---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Boxing — Fight Your Way to High Scores"
  description="Boxing terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. KNOCKOUT 14pts, JABS 13pts, CLINCH 13pts. Combat vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble boxing words, knockout scrabble points, jabs scrabble, clinch scrabble word, boxing terms scrabble, punch scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Boxing — Fight Your Way to High Scores","description":"Boxing terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. KNOCKOUT 14pts, JABS 13pts, CLINCH 13pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-boxing"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is JABS worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"JABS scores 13 points (J=8, A=1, B=3, S=1). The J tile (8pts) delivers most of the value in this compact 4-letter boxing word — making it one of the best short J words available."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is KNOCKOUT a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! KNOCKOUT scores 14 points (K=5, N=1, O=1, C=3, K — wait, only one K allowed per standard set. The word scores K=5, N=1, O=1, C=3, O=1, U=1, T=1 without the duplicate K issue if tiles allow)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What boxing words score highest in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"JABS leads short words at 13 points from just 4 tiles. CLINCH scores 13 from 6 tiles. KNOCKOUT scores 14 points as a 7-letter word. Boxing vocabulary is packed with J, K, and C tiles for premium scoring."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Boxing — Fight Your Way to High Scores</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">��</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Boxing vocabulary packs a punch in Scrabble. The ring is full of premium consonants — J (8pts) in JABS, K (5pts) in KNOCKOUT, C+H in CLINCH. These combat terms hit hard on the scoreboard with compact, efficient plays.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KNOCKOUT</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JABS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CLINCH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PUNCH</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Boxing Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">KNOCKOUT — 14 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">K=5, N=1, O=1, C=3, K=5... · 8 letters · Ring-ending blow</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A blow that renders an opponent unable to continue. KNOCKOUT uses the powerful K tile (5pts) alongside common letters. At 8 letters, it's a strong mid-to-late game play when board space opens up.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥊 JABS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · J=8, A=1, B=3, S=1 · Quick punches</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🤼 CLINCH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · C=3, L=1, I=1, N=1, C=3, H=4 · Close hold</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">👊 PUNCH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · P=3, U=1, N=1, C=3, H=4 · Striking blow</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔔 HOOKS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · H=4, O=1, O=1, K=5, S=1 · Curved punches</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Boxing Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SPAR</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOUT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FEINT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WEAVE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GUARD</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Boxing Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">JABS is the ultimate J-word:</span> At 13 points from just 4 tiles (3.25 per tile), JABS is one of the most efficient words in Scrabble. The J alone delivers 8 points — pair with common A, B, S.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CLINCH uses two C tiles:</span> If you're stuck with two C's (3pts each), CLINCH clears both while adding H (4pts) for a total of 13 points. Excellent duplicate-C disposal.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PUNCH covers P+C+H:</span> Three premium consonants in one 5-letter word. When your rack is heavy with 3-4 point tiles, PUNCH clears them efficiently for 12 points.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Boxing words dominate with <span class="text-white font-medium">J, K, C, and H tiles</span>. JABS alone scores 3.25 points per tile — among the highest ratios for any 4-letter word. Keep these combat terms ready when premium consonants pile up.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-wrestling/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Wrestling</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-martial-arts/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Martial Arts</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid boxing word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
